# Web Auth And Supabase

- Browser code may use the public Supabase client and public env vars only.
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to client code, shared packages consumed by the client, or browser-visible logs.
- Server-only admin operations belong in route handlers or server-only modules.
- The web app depends on `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and server-side admin flows also depend on `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`.
- When changing auth flows, avoid logged-out experiences that render `null` or blank screens before redirecting.
- Respect Supabase RLS assumptions when changing queries, inserts, and updates.
